"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-football-kylian-mbappe-olympics-paris-lionel-messi-real-madrid-b2563828.html\", \"text\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Mbappe has ruled out featuring for the hosts at Paris 2024 after his summer switch to the Spanish capital  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent. Read ourPrivacy notice  Kylian Mbappeconfirmed on Sunday he will not play forFrance'sOlympic team atParis 2024as his new clubReal Madridare against the idea.  The 25-year-old said in March that he waskeen on playing at his home Gamesbut since the Olympic soccer tournament is not onFifa's calendar clubs arenot obliged to release their players.  Mbappe was not included in a 25-man preliminary squad for theOlympicsearlier this month, though head coach Thierry Henry left the door open.  \\\"My club's position was very clear, so from that moment on, I think I (knew) I will not be taking part in the Games,\\\" Mbappe told reporters ahead of Monday's Group D match against Austria atEuro 2024.  \\\"That's just the way it is, and I understand that too. I am joining a new team in September, so it's not the best way to start an adventure.  \\\"I am going to wish this French team all the best. I am going to watch every game. I hope they will win the gold medal.\\\"  The men's Olympic football competition begins on July 24, 10 days after the Euro 2024 final, and ends on August 9.  Lionel Messihas alsoruled himself out of the tournamentdespite receiving an invite from Argentina boss, and former teammate, Javier Mascherano.  The Inter Miami forward admitted that the event would be \\\"too much\\\" in a summer that also includes a Copa America.  Reuters  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\"}"